-- Australia shares jump 2 pct in 4th straight session of gains
-- 
-- Mon Dec 22, 2014 12:59AM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Dec 22 (Reuters) - Australian shares rose for the fourth consecutive session on Monday in a holiday-shortened week, led energy and resources companies in a broad-based rally that reflected a rebound in oil prices and risk appetite. [ID:nL3N0U618I]

The S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO> jumped 2 percent, or 103.35 points, to 5,442 at the close of trade. The benchmark advanced 2.5 percent on Friday, the biggest one-day gain since July 2013.